The House Committee on Judiciary, Non-Civil offers the following substitute to HB 242:
A BILL TO BE ENTITLED
AN ACT
1 To amend Code Section 16-11-34.2 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to
2 disorderly or disruptive conduct at any funeral or memorial service, so as to include religious
3 worship and observance; to provide for related matters; to repeal conflicting laws; and for
4 other purposes.
5 BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF GEORGIA:
6 SECTION 1.
7 Code Section 16-11-34.2 of the Official Code of Georgia Annotated, relating to disorderly
8 or disruptive conduct at any funeral or memorial service, is amended by revising subsection
9 (a) and the introductory language of subsection (b) as follows:
10 "(a) The General Assembly declares that the interest of persons in planning, participating
11 in, and attending a religious worship or observance, or a funeral or memorial service for
12 a deceased relative or loved one, without unwanted impediment, disruption, disturbance,
13 or interference is a substantial interest and the General Assembly further recognizes the
14 need to impose content neutral time, place, and manner restrictions on unwanted acts
15 carried out with the intent to impede, disrupt, disturb, or interfere with such funeral
16 worship, observance, funeral, or memorial service.
